## 3. Salt DS Rules

### Button API (from GitHub `jpmorganchase/salt-ds`)
```tsx
// âś… Correct
<Button sentiment="accented" appearance="solid">Label</Button>

// âťŚ Wrong â€” these are NOT Salt appearances
<Button appearance="filled" />     // Use "solid"
<Button appearance="outlined" />   // Use "bordered"  
<Button appearance="text" />       // Use "transparent"
```
- **Appearances:** `solid` | `bordered` | `transparent`
- **Sentiments:** `accented` | `neutral` | `positive` | `caution` | `negative`

### Input API
```tsx
<FormField validationStatus="error">
  <FormFieldLabel>Label</FormFieldLabel>
  <Input variant="primary" bordered={false} />
  <FormFieldHelperText>Error message</FormFieldHelperText>
</FormField>
```
- **Variants:** `primary` | `secondary` | `tertiary`
- **bordered** prop for full-border mode

### Spacing (4px grid, density-responsive)
```
--salt-spacing-100: 4px(H) / 8px(M) / 12px(L) / 16px(T)
--salt-spacing-200: 8px(H) / 16px(M) / 24px(L) / 32px(T)
```

### Corner Radius (density-responsive)
```
--salt-curve-100: 2px(H) / 4px(M) / 6px(L) / 8px(T)
```

### Component Height
```
--salt-size-base: 20px(H) / 28px(M) / 36px(L) / 44px(T)
```

### Dark Mode
- Accent text uses `accentText` token (teal-400 `#4CA1C2`, 6.12:1) not accent (teal-500 `#1B7F9E`, 3.90:1)
- Named backgrounds: snow/marble/limestone â†’ jet/granite/leather

